title.rendered: Inner-city living and a perfect lifestyle!

content.rendered:
This stylish two-bedroom apartment is situated in the Canberra city precinct, perfect for you to experience the convenience of a vibrant inner-city life.

The apartment itself celebrates open plan living, with a kitchen featuring high end appliances and stone bench tops. An inviting dining and lounge area opens out to a great sized balcony, providing ample space to enjoy outdoor entertaining. Offering two spacious bedrooms both with built in robes. The master bedroom has its own ensuite and the main bathroom is luxurious in design.

With only a short stroll to an abundance of leisure and social attractions such as restaurants, cafes, bars, cinemas, the Canberra centre, and the light rail, you simply cannot get an easier lifestyle than this.

Features

Two spacious bedrooms, main with ensuite
Open plan living and dining
Great size kitchen with quality stainless steel appliances
Balcony with great views
Roof top outdoor entertaining terrace
Lift access and visitor intercom
Convenient location
Walking distance to an abundance of leisure and social interactions
Light rail and Canberra centre is just a short stroll away close by

This is a rare opportunity to come by so act quick and secure this off-the -plan luxury apartment for yourself now.

title.rendered: Great Opportunity in landmark Dusk for investor & owner occupier

content.rendered:
A landmark development in the evolving Belconnen Town Centre, perfect for the wise investor.
Dusk packs a punch for a competitive price. An open living and dining area for entertainment and an easy connected layout make this 2 bedroom, 2 bathroom apartment an attractive opportunity.

Enjoying a northern aspect with uninterrupted views of Lake Ginniderra from the balcony, this unit boasts a functional and simple design. It has quality SMEG appliances in the kitchen and stylish finishes throughout which set this property apart from others in its category.

Dusk enjoys a superb lakefront location, with five star amenities within walking distance. The complex has been designed to offer a space to entertain, exclusive to its residents, the level 14 common area, offers private cooking, dining and leisure facilities.
Dusk’s lower levels will be occupied by top commercial tenants including Woolworths Metro, plus five star dining thanks to Trecento, BZB and No.10, with more to come.

Tenancy Information
The property is currently tenanted for $500 per week in a fixed term until November 2021, however this can be negotiated.

Summary of features:
* 75 m2 living space
* 8 m2 balcony
* 6.0 star EER
* Balcony with uninterrupted lake views
* High quality appliances and finishes
* High investment yields
* SMEG appliances (oven, cooktop, dishwasher, rangehood)
* LED downlights throughout
* Secure basement parking
* Intercom access

Strata: $2,800/year
Rates: $350/quarter
Land Tax: $410/quarter

title.rendered: A Dream Location Packed with Potential!

content.rendered:
Situated in the Emerald Terrace Complex above the popular Amaroo Town Centre, this two-bedroom home would suit first home buyers or those looking to add a quality property to their investment portfolio. Everything you need is only a few steps away, including Coles, gyms, plenty of food outlets, cafes and much more. In addition to all that, the Gungahlin town centre and Casey marketplace are both just a short drive away.

North facing and set over three levels, this quality terrace home is spacious light filled and very modern. The kitchen has quality stainless steel appliances, stone bench tops and ample cupboard space for your everyday cooking convenience.

Heading upstairs to the third level, you will be greeted with two good sized bedrooms, the master featuring its own ensuite with a huge built in robe with mirrored sliding doors. The second bedroom is complimented by the main bathroom adding convenience and privacy to your lifestyle.
Finally there is a spare rumpus/bedroom downstairs, accessible from the double garage.

This is a great home or investment, so come in and inspect today.

Features:

* Two good size rooms with built in robes
* Main bedroom has its own ensuite
* Additional rumpus or bedroom on the ground floor
* Spacious open plan living
* Central kitchen with stainless steel appliances and stone bench tops
* Two balconies one on each side of the home
* RC air conditioning in the main living area
* RC air conditioning the master bedroom
* Outlook to Reserve
* All your shopping needs are right downstairs
* Short drive to Gungahlin town centre and Casey market town

Rates: $1404.66 pa
Land Tax: $1706.61 pa
Built: 2017
Total Living: 172sqm
Body Corp: $637.55 pq

title.rendered: Flexible living for the extended family

content.rendered:
Auction Location: On Site.

Conveniently located in the popular suburb of Harrison, a rare opportunity has become available for you to purchase this versatile family home for the extended family. This would be a perfect investment If you are looking for a multipurpose floor plan that can be completely sectioned into two separate family homes.

Upon entry, you will be welcomed by a spacious formal lounge perfectly designed for your everyday entertaining needs. Adjoining this appealing living space, you have two separate studies which could be utilised as a home office, extra storage or guest room. The potential on what you can do with these two rooms is unlimited.

Featuring five bedrooms, four with built in robes and the master with a walk-in robe and ensuite. The first section of the home consists of three bedrooms, formal lounge, combined living and dining and a versatile kitchen with plenty of cupboard space. The second part of the home is serviced by two other bedrooms, a good size bathroom, dining area, spacious lounge/rumpus room and a full-sized kitchen. Space and privacy will never be an issue with this family home.

Located only a few minutes’ walk to the light rail stop, Harrison School, Franklin shops which consists of Woolworths, medical centres and food outlets. The Gungahlin Town Centre is only a short drive away and close enough to even take a stroll there on a nice sunny day.

This is a rare one to come by so don’t miss out on the opportunity to secure a family home that has so much to offer.

* Land Tax: $3527.25pa
